VI. The last formal part of a charter which it is necessary for me to note are the Subscriptions or Teste. The Roman law appears not to have re- quired signatures3 the presence of the witnesses being held to be sufficient to authenticate a document. How lar this principle prevailed in the church I will not take upon mysell to say: but in almost all ecclesiastical instruments we find the witnesses sub· scribing with their own hands.
